15. Final verdict

This is the correct first source after Corbin’s already-completed pieces.

It gives Imaginarium a strong root-engine:

the soul is exiled in the Occident of matter; the world is a crypt; taʾwīl unlocks the crypt by interpreting the soul; the Angel appears as guide; the soul becomes bird, emigrant, companion, and traveler; the journey turns toward the Orient, but final liberation remains suspended as invitation.

Use this source not for mass quotation, but for architecture.

