14. Balance review

This source needs two simultaneous readings:

Sympathetic reading

Rūzbihān is a major witness to the lived force of unveiling, divine beauty, angelic encounter, and ecstatic speech.

Critical reading

The text is also a literary self-presentation. The visionary does not simply “report experiences”; he organizes them into a sanctified life story.

The companion must preserve both:

the intensity of the visions
