1. Source identity

Primary source: ʿAbd al-Karīm al-Jīlī, al-Insān al-Kāmil fī Maʿrifat al-Awākhir wa-l-Awāʾil — The Perfect Human in the Knowledge of Things Last and First.

Why this comes after the first ten: the original queue is complete, so the next best Corbin-lineage / Akbarian source is al-Jīlī. The Ibn Arabi Society describes him as a major Ibn ʿArabī-lineage metaphysician, born in 1365, active mainly in Zabid, Yemen, and famous for developing the doctrine of the Perfect Human.

