2. Master structural reading

Al-Jīlī systematizes what Ibn ʿArabī and Shabistarī opened: the human as the total mirror of reality.

The core movement:

The Real manifests through degrees of being.
The cosmos is a vast unfolding of divine names and presences.
The Perfect Human gathers all degrees into one complete form.
The Muhammadan Reality is the supreme form of this perfection.

A recent scholarly article states that for Ibn ʿArabī’s school, the Perfect Human is both the boundary and portal between the divine absolute and created being, the culmination of divine self-disclosure, the summit of spiritual realization, and always identical in underlying reality with the timeless spirit of the Prophet Muḥammad.

3. Part / chapter map

Al-Jīlī’s work has 63 chapters. A 2024 scholarly overview notes that only chapter 60 is explicitly devoted to the Perfect Human, but al-Jīlī says that this chapter is the “mainstay” of the whole book and that the whole work explains it.

So the companion should treat the book as:

Layer	Function
