After Simnānī’s subtle-centre and anti-careless-unity correction, Jāmī is the right next source because he gives a clean, compact, public-domain Akbarian synthesis.

His function:

Ibn ʿArabī’s ocean becomes thirty flashes: short metaphysical illuminations, each compressing unity, manifestation, love, poverty, selfhood, unveiling, and the Real into a prose-poem unit.

This is useful for Imaginarium because it is source-rich but manageable. It can become a modular essay/passage-pack engine.

